The paper focuses on improving the performance of data center networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper specifically addresses the issue of tail latency, which is a common problem in data center networks (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the implementation of RepNet, which is an application layer transport protocol, and therefore falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of RepNet's performance, which involves analyzing data and making conclusions based on that data, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and architecture (cs.AR).
